<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF107-983-100  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 983 100.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Network World  Dec 18 1989 v6 n50 p18(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Banks opting for platform automation.andM;</TITLE><TEXT><ABSTRACT>A majority of banks is choosing platform automation over all othernetwork technology options.andP;  Platform automation allows localbranches remote access to a headquarters mainframe through anetwork of microcomputers at the local branch.andP;  Customerinformation is kept on the host computer.andP;  A Bank AdministrationInstitute survey found that banks have spent an average of$174,800 each year on platform automation equipment.andP;  By 1992 thefigure is expected to nearly double to $338,000.andP;  Banks will alsospend an average of $528,000 per year over the same three-yearperiod on upgrades of their host processors and data base softwareto support platform automation.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     BankingAutomationLocal Area NetworksCommunications EquipmentUser SurveyBank Administration InstituteStrategic PlanningUpgrading.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>